  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Investigating Font Integration**\n\nI\'m now determining the best approach for integrating Google Fonts. I\'m considering modifying `index.html` or importing directly into `/src/index.css`. The CSS file already imports Tailwind, so I can keep things clean if I can import the fonts in that file. I just found a React setup guide showing the `@import url` method for adding fonts.\n\n\n**Confirming Tailwind Configuration**\n\nI\'ve verified that Tailwind v4 is indeed active through the `package.json` file. I\'ve also confirmed that font configuration in Tailwind v4 is directly within the main CSS using the `@theme` block. I reviewed `index.html` to see if there were any surprises, and it looks straightforward. Now, I\'m ready to proceed with integrating the desired fonts directly into `index.css` using the `@theme` block, and the font import statements.\n\n\n**Refining Application Architecture**\n\nI\'m now establishing the core architecture. I\'m focusing on screen organization within the React app. I\'m assigning file names based on keys and universes and identifying screens. I\'ve designed a home screen universe (\"L\'Origine\") with two blocks linking to \"La Ligne Femme\" and \"La Prestance Homme.\" I\'m evaluating a premium navigation bar, possibly a sidebar or bottom pill bar, for seamless user navigation between universes.\n\n\n**Defining App Universes**\n\nI\'m now integrating new universes and establishing connections. The \"Origine\" screen will serve as a home entryway, linking to \"Haute Couture,\" \"L\'\303\211crin,\" \"L\'H\303\251ritage,\" and the full \"Le Panier\" shopping cart. I\'m excited about this clean, integrated boutique app, making items like the \"Manteau Architecte\" instantly accessible and updating the cart in real-time. I\'m focusing on high-end typography and user interaction.\n\n\n**Defining Product Details**\n\nI\'m now detailing a product: the \"Manteau Architecte.\" This urban elegance piece features asymmetric lines and pronounced shoulders for a statuesque presence. Designed with carefully selected rigid materials to hold its architectural form, I\'m noting sizes (34, 36, 38) and specifying that size 40 is unavailable. I\'ve also identified three image URLs for the product display.\n\n\n**Cataloging New Products**\n\nI\'m now cataloging new products for the boutique. I\'ve added the \"Blazer Monolithe\" at 980\342\202\254, described as a sculpted blazer with contrasting seams, and the \"Robe Structure\" at 1200\342\202\254, a sculptural, pleated dress with asymmetrical draping. I\'m focusing on concise descriptions and relevant image URLs to ensure clear product representation.\n\n\n\n**Adding New Products**\n\nI\'m now detailing new boutique products. I\'ve added \"Sac G\303\251om\303\251trie\" for 650\342\202\254 to Screen 6, described as a structured leather bag with clean, asymmetrical lines. I\'m also including two necklaces in the Fine Jewelry (Joaillerie et Accessoires) collection: \"Collier de l\'Aube\" and \"Collier de Perles Douces,\" both for 185\342\202\254 on Screens 7 and 9. I\'m focused on concise product details.\n\n\n**Describing Jewelry Details**\n\nI\'m now detailing a new jewelry piece, \"Collier Perles Douces,\" priced at 185\342\202\254. It\'s a delicate necklace featuring a selection of pearls. I have identified image URLs and descriptions for each piece. Next I will add \"Bague Perle d\'Aube\" to screen 3 and 8 at 240\342\202\254. I\'m focusing on concisely capturing the details of each item.\n\n\n\n**Adding New Jewelry**\n\nI\'m now detailing more jewelry pieces. I\'ve added \"Collier Goutte\" for 320\342\202\254, and \"Collier Fil de Soie\" for 315\342\202\254, both on Screen 8. The first features a delicate gold drop and pearl, while the second is a fine silk thread necklace. I\'m focusing on concise descriptions and relevant image URLs.\n\n\n**Adding New Jewelry**\n\nI\'ve just added \"Cr\303\251oles Murmure\" and \"Cr\303\251oles Brume,\" sculptural gold cr\303\251oles at 180\342\202\254 and 210\342\202\254 respectively, to Screens 3 and 8. The jewelry descriptions highlight a timeless, minimalist design. I\'ve also integrated the image URLs.\n\n\n**Adding New Jewelry**\n\nI\'ve just added \"Pendentif Soie\" to Screen 8 for 280\342\202\254, a minimalist pendant resembling a golden silk cell. I\'ve also incorporated the image URL. Additionally, I\'ve added \"Bague Perle\" and \"Bague Aurore\" to Screens 8 and 7, respectively, for 510\342\202\254 and 120\342\202\254, describing these as a freshwater pearl set on an exclusive gold twist. I\'ve included the image URL as well.\n\n\n**Adding Final Jewelry Pieces**\n\nI\'ve just added the \"Bracelet \303\211treinte\" to Screen 8 for 340\342\202\254. It\'s a woven gold bracelet designed to gently embrace the wrist. I have finalized the jewelry descriptions, incorporating image URLs for all the pieces. I\'ve finished the jewelry integration.\n\n\n**Adding New Abayas**\n\nI\'ve just added two new abayas. \"The Silk Abaya,\" a flowing sand silk abaya priced at 185\342\202\254, and \"The Heritage Meulfeu,\" an olive green draped abaya at 220\342\202\254, are both now on Screen 10. I\'ve focused on capturing the essence of each piece and have integrated the image URLs.\n\n\n**Adding New Fabrics**\n\nI\'ve just added two new fabric pieces for Screen 10. \"The Tailored Set\" is now available for 280\342\202\254, a flowing, charcoal suit. I\'ve also incorporated the image URL. The \"Chiffon Drape,\" a translucent silk chiffon veil priced at 160\342\202\254, is also added, with the relevant image URL included.\n\n\n**Structuring App Data**\n\nI\'m now focusing on organizing app data and types for the boutique application. I\'ve decided to create `/src/types.ts` to define product structures, cart and active universe states, and am now working on `/src/data`. I\'m going to create a directory for each universe.\n\n\n**Defining App File Structure**\n\nI\'m now establishing core application components with individual files and screens. I\'m focusing on defining component structures for each screen. I am now working on `/src/components/TopAppBar.tsx` to handle the top navigation bar, and `/src/components/BottomNav.tsx` for the floating bottom navigation. I\'m also planning the `UniversalCart.tsx`, catalog views, the \"OrigineEntry.tsx\", and I am striving for modularity.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 35
      nanos: 952170225
    }
