          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              {/* Vertical side banner text */}"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              <div className=\"absolute right-0 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 rotate-95 origin-center transform translate-x-2\">"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "                <p className=\"text-[10px] italic text-[#b84b14] font-medium tracking-widest whitespace-nowrap\">"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "                  Archives, Dakar 1988"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "                </p>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              </div>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "            </div>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "            {/* Rich editorial text block */}"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "            <div className=\"border-l border-[#A8A39D]/30 pl-5 pr-1 py-1 text-[#2C2825]/90\">"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              <p className=\"text-sm leading-[1.85] text-justify mb-8 font-light\">"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "                <span className=\"float-left text-5xl font-serif text-[#b84b14] leading-none pr-3 pt-1\">T</span>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "                rue elegance is rarely learned; it is inherited. It lives in the quiet moments of observation, watching a mother drape her meulfeu with a practiced, almost unconscious grace. Every fold tells a story of dignity, resilience, and an understated power that requires no volume to be heard."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              </p>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              <p className=\"text-sm leading-[1.85] text-justify mb-8 font-light\">"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "                Myriam Veil was born not from a desire to create fashion, but from a necessity to preserve a feeling. The feeling of being enveloped in history, of wearing one\342\200\231s values as a second skin. Marieme Fall, my mother, was the architect of this sentiment. Her approach to modesty was never restrictive; it was her most profound expression of freedom and self-respect."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              </p>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              <p className=\"text-sm leading-[1.85] text-justify mb-12 font-light\">"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "                We design with these memories woven into every thread. We favor the raw honesty of natural fibers, the architecture of asymmetric cuts, and the earthy palettes of the landscapes that shaped her. This is not mere clothing. It is an editorial translation of legacy\342\200\224a wearable archive for the modern woman who understands that the most compelling statement is often a whisper."
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "              </p>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "            </div>"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
        lines {
          text: "            {/* Story prose catalog entryway */}"
          type: UNIFIED_DIFF_LINE_TYPE_INSERT
        }
