    thinking: "**Considering Immersive UI Styling**\n\nI\'m now integrating the Immersive UI styling into the Couture product catalog. Specifically, I\'m adjusting the general container color to `bg-[#f8f7f6]` with `text-[#050505]`. The existing structure for filters, product grids, details pages, and sizes remains in place, but I\'m updating their appearance.\n\n\n**Refining Aesthetic Details**\n\nI\'ve updated the filter and subheader. Specifically, the background is now `bg-white/[0.01] border-b border-white/10 backdrop-blur-md`, and the text and border styling is `text-slate-300 hover:text-blue-400 border-white/5 hover:border-blue-400`. For the filter chips, I\'ve swapped to transparent backgrounds and updated the active and inactive button states to look cleaner and more consistent. The product card appearance has also been modernized with a dark slate background, rounded corners and a slight shadow.\n\n\n**Updating Visual Consistency**\n\nI\'m focused on harmonizing the visual language of the product details screen with the updated card and filter elements. I\'ve preserved grayscale imagery on the product cards, enhancing them with full color and a slight zoom on hover. I\'m updating the card text to slate-200 with hover blue, category to slate-500, and price to blue or violet, to highlight this information. I\'m also implementing pagination with translucent styling. Further, I\'ve modernized the product detail sub-header and gallery with a dark theme.\n\n\n**Implementing Detail Components**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the size selection components within the product detail view. I\'m styling the size selection with slate-400 labels, while active size buttons are now blue-600 with white text and a blue-500 border. Inactive buttons have a white/5 background, slate-300 text, and a white/10 border. Out-of-stock buttons are styled with slate-600 text, a dark background, a white/5 border, and a line-through effect at 40% opacity. I\'m also styling accordions, the bottom CTA, and now I\'m prepping to update the CollectionCouture component.\n\n\n\n"
